\ log is base-10, ln is natural, ^ is polymorphic power ( base exp -- base^exp ).

\ ---- log base-10 ----
100 log .            \ 2
1000 log .           \ 3
1 log .              \ 0

\ ---- ln natural ----
1 ln .               \ 0
1 exp ln .           \ 1  (ln of e)

\ ---- ^ : scalar ----
2 10 ^ .             \ 1024
9 0.5 ^ .            \ 3
2 -1 ^ .             \ 0.5
5 0 ^ .              \ 1

\ ---- ^ : matrix ^ scalar (element-wise) ----
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix 2 ^ .           \ [1 4 9 16]

\ ---- ^ : scalar ^ matrix ----
2 [ 0 1 2 3 ] 1 4 matrix ^ .           \ [1 2 4 8]

\ ---- ^ : matrix ^ matrix (element-wise, same shape) ----
[ 2 3 4 ] 1 3 matrix  [ 3 2 1 ] 1 3 matrix  ^ .   \ [8 9 4]

\ ---- failures ----
"x" 2 ^
[ 1 2 ] 1 2 matrix  [ 1 2 3 ] 1 3 matrix  ^

clear
\ % is Forth /mod: ( a b -- rem quot ), quotient on top.
\ Printing with `. .` shows quotient first (top of stack), then remainder.

17 5 % . . cr        \ 3 2     (quot 3, rem 2)
7 3 % . . cr         \ 2 1
-7 3 % . . cr        \ -2 -1   (remainder takes the sign of the dividend)
10 2 % . . cr        \ 5 0
5.5 2 % . . cr       \ 2 1.5

\ remainder alone (mod) via drop; quotient alone via swap drop
7 3 % drop . cr      \ 1   (the remainder)
7 3 % swap drop . cr \ 2   (the quotient)

\ min2/max2: lt-ordered lesser and greater of two scalars
3 7 min2 . cr        \ 3
7 3 min2 . cr        \ 3
3 7 max2 . cr        \ 7
7 3 max2 . cr        \ 7
-2 -5 min2 . cr      \ -5
4 4 max2 . cr        \ 4
"apple" "pear" min2 . cr \ apple  (lt is structural on strings)

\ failures
5 0 %
"x" 2 %

clear
\ Monomorphic float-only ops (f-prefixed): no tag check, depth-guarded.
\ The polymorphic versions (abs, sqrt, +, ^, ...) are tested elsewhere; these
\ are the fast unsafe counterparts and must match on float inputs.

\ unary functions
-3.0 fabs . cr        \ 3
9.0 fsqrt . cr        \ 3
0.0 fexp . cr         \ 1
1.0 fln . cr          \ 0
1000.0 flog . cr      \ 3
0.0 fsin . cr         \ 0
0.0 fcos . cr         \ 1
1.0 fatan . cr        \ 0.785398
2.7 fround . cr       \ 3
2.1 fround-up . cr    \ 3
2.9 fround-down . cr  \ 2
-2.9 ftruncate . cr   \ -2
5.0 fnegate . cr      \ -5
5.0 f1+ . cr          \ 6
5.0 f1- . cr          \ 4
5.0 fsq . cr          \ 25

\ binary
2.0 10.0 f^ . cr      \ 1024
-7.0 3.0 fmod . cr    \ -1
2.0 3.0 f+ . cr       \ 5
10.0 4.0 f- . cr      \ 6
3.0 4.0 f* . cr       \ 12
12.0 4.0 f/ . cr      \ 3

\ f++ / f-- : unsafe float local increment / decrement (immediate; named local)
: finc | n |  0 to n  f++ n  f++ n  f++ n  n ;
finc . cr             \ 3
: fdec | n |  10 to n  f-- n  f-- n  n ;
fdec . cr             \ 8
: fmix |> x |  f++ x  f-- x  f-- x  x ;
5 fmix . cr           \ 4
: fnest | n |  0 to n  [: f++ n :] execute  n ;   \ outer local via depth-path fallback
fnest . cr            \ 1

\ depth guard (empty stack)
fsqrt
